21:52:30.967Z\",\"uuid\":\"98236bdb-d39b-423d-afb9-23b8e09c47c4\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"f6818eff-c752-44c0-8e32-2cbe0d928bfb\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"700a9d25-a758-466b-a469-b245a17d8b55\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage\",\"slug\":\"smooth-foraging-hollerith\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01XLj4preTeAhSQUchcufKuk\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→---\\n     2→name: e2e-triage\\n     3→description: Triage E2E test failures — run locally with mise or via CI re-runs, classify flaky vs real bug, create PRs for flaky fixes and GitHub issues for real bugs\\n     4→---\\n     5→\\n     6→# E2E Triage\\n     7→\\n     8→Triage E2E test failures with **re-run verification**. Operates in two modes (auto-detected), analyzes artifacts, re-runs failing tests to distinguish flaky from real bugs, then takes action: batched PR for flaky fixes, GitHub issues for real bugs.\\n     9→\\n    10→## Mode Detection\\n    11→\\n    12→- **CI mode**: `WORKFLOW_RUN_ID` env var is set (injected by `e2e-triage.yml`)\\n    13→- **Local mode**: No `WORKFLOW_RUN_ID` — user invokes `/e2e-triage` manually\\n    14→\\n    15→---\\n    16→\\n    17→## Local Mode\\n    18→\\n    19→### Step L1: Parse User Input\\n    20→\\n    21→The user provides one or more of:\\n    22→- **Test name(s)** — e.g., `TestInteractiveMultiStep`\\n    23→- **`--agent <agent>`** — optional, defaults to all agents that previously failed\\n    24→- **A local artifact path** — skip straight to analysis of existing artifacts\\n    25→\\n    26→**Cost warning:** Real E2E tests consume API tokens. Before running, confirm with the user unless they provided specific test names (implying intent to run).\\n    27→\\n    28→### Step L2: First Run\\n    29→\\n    30→```bash\\n    31→mise run test:e2e --agent <agent> <TestName>\\n    32→```\\n    33→\\n    34→Capture the artifact directory from the `artifacts: <path>` output line.\\n    35→\\n    36→### Step L3: Re-run on Failure\\n    37→\\n    38→If the test **passes** on first run: report as passing, done for this test.\\n    39→\\n    40→If the test **fails**: run a **second time** with the same parameters.\\n    41→\\n    42→### Step L4: Tiebreaker (if needed)\\n    43→\\n    44→If results are **split** (1 pass, 1 fail): run a **third time** as tiebreaker.\\n    45→\\n    46→### Step L5: Collect Results\\n    47→\\n    48→For each test+agent pair, record: `(test, agent, run_1_result, run_2_result, [run_3_result])`\\n    49→\\n    50→Proceed to **Shared Analysis** (Step 1 below).\\n    51→\\n    52→---\\n    53→\\n    54→## CI Mode\\n    55→\\n    56→### Step C1: Download Artifacts\\n    57→\\n    58→**If given a run ID, URL, or \\\"latest\\\":**\\n    59→```bash\\n    60→artifact_dir=$(scripts/download-e2e-artifacts.sh <input>)\\n    61→```\\n    62→\\n    63→**If `WORKFLOW_RUN_ID` is set (automated trigger):**\\n    64→```bash\\n    65→artifact_dir=\\\"e2e/artifacts/ci-${WORKFLOW_RUN_ID}\\\"\\n    66→```\\n    67→\\n    68→The download step in the workflow has already placed artifacts there.\\n    69→\\n    70→### Step C2: Identify Failures\\n    71→\\n    72→For each agent subdirectory in the artifact root:\\n    73→1. Read `report.nocolor.txt` — list failed tests with error messages, file:line references\\n    74→2. Skip agents with zero failures\\n    75→3. Build failure list: `[(test_name, agent, error_line, duration, file:line)]`\\n    76→\\n    77→### Step C3: Re-run Failing Tests via CI\\n    78→\\n    79→For each failing test+agent pair, **sequentially**:\\n    80→\\n    81→1. **Trigger re-run:**\\n    82→   ```bash\\n    83→   gh workflow run e2e-isolated.yml -f agent=<agent> -f test=<TestName>\\n    84→   ```\\n    85→\\n    86→2. **Wait for run to register** (~5s), then find the run ID:\\n    87→   ```bash\\n    88→   gh run list -w e2e-isolated.yml -L 1 --json databaseId -q '.[0].databaseId'\\n    89→   ```\\n    90→\\n    91→3. **Poll until complete** (check every 30s, timeout after 25 minutes):\\n    92→   ```bash\\n    93→   gh run view <run-id> --json status,conclusion\\n    94→   ```\\n    95→\\n    96→4. **Download re-run artifacts:**\\n    97→   ```bash\\n    98→   gh run download <run-id> --dir <rerun-artifact-dir>\\n    99→   ```\\n   100→\\n   101→5. **Repeat for a second re-run** (same test+agent).\\n   102→\\n   103→### Step C4: Collect Results\\n   104→\\n   105→For each test+agent pair, record: `(test, agent, original_result, rerun_1_result, rerun_2_result)`\\n   106→\\n   107→Proceed to **Shared Analysis** (Step 1 below).\\n   108→\\n   109→---\\n   110→\\n   111→## Shared Analysis & Classification\\n   112→\\n   113→### Step 1: Analyze Each Failure\\n   114→\\n   115→For each failure, examine available artifacts:\\n   116→\\n   117→1. **Read `console.log`** — what did the agent actually do? Full chronological transcript.\\n   118→2. **Read test source at file:line** — what was expected?\\n   119→3. **Read `entire-logs/entire.log`** — any CLI errors, panics, unexpected behavior?\\n   120→4. **Read `git-log.txt` / `git-tree.txt`** — repo state at failure time\\n   121→5. **Read `checkpoint-metadata/`** — corrupt or missing metadata?\\n   122→\\n   123→### Step 2: Classify Each Failure\\n   124→\\n   125→Use **re-run results as the primary signal**, supplemented by artifact analysis.\\n   126→\\n   127→#### Re-run signals (strongest):\\n   128→\\n   129→| Original | Re-run 1 | Re-run 2 | Classification |\\n   130→|----------|----------|----------|----------------|\\n   131→| FAIL | FAIL (same error) | FAIL (same error) | **real-bug** |\\n   132→| FAIL | PASS | PASS | **flaky** |\\n   133→| FAIL | PASS | FAIL | **flaky** (non-deterministic) |\\n   134→| FAIL | FAIL | PASS | **flaky** (non-deterministic) |\\n   135→| FAIL | FAIL (different error) | FAIL (different error) | **needs deeper analysis** — examine artifacts |\\n   136→\\n   137→#### Strong `real-bug` signals (supplement re-runs):\\n   138→\\n   139→- `entire.log` contains `\\\"level\\\":\\\"ERROR\\\"` or panic/stack traces\\n   140→- Checkpoint metadata structurally corrupt (malformed JSON, missing `checkpoint_id`/`strategy`)\\n   141→- Session state file missing or malformed when expected\\n   142→- Hooks did not fire at all (no `hook invoked` log entries)\\n   143→- Shadow/metadata branch has wrong tree structure\\n   144→- Same test fails across 3+ agents with same non-timeout symptom\\n   145→- Error references CLI code (panic in `cmd/entire/cli/`)\\n   146→\\n   147→#### Strong `flaky` signals (unless overridden by real-bug):\\n   148→\\n   149→- `signal: killed` (timeout)\\n   150→- `context deadline exceeded` or `WaitForCheckpoint.*exceeded deadline`\\n   151→- Agent asked for confirmation instead of acting\\n   152→- Agent created file at wrong path / wrong name\\n   153→- Agent produced no output\\n   154→- Agent committed when it shouldn't have (or vice versa)\\n   155→- Duration near timeout limit\\n   156→\\n   157→#### Ambiguous cases:\\n   158→\\n   159→Read `entire.log` carefully:\\n   160→- If hooks fired correctly and metadata is valid -> lean **flaky**\\n   161→- If hooks fired but produced wrong results -> lean **real-bug**\\n   162→\\n   163→### Step 3: Cross-Agent Correlation\\n   164→\\n   165→Before acting, check correlations using re-run data:\\n   166→- Same test fails for 3+ agents, all re-runs also fail -> strong **real-bug**\\n   167→- Same test fails for multiple agents, but re-runs pass -> **flaky** (shared prompt issue)\\n   168→- One agent fails consistently, others pass -> agent-specific issue (still **real-bug** if re-runs confirm)\\n   169→\\n   170→### Step 4: Take Action\\n   171→\\n   172→#### For `flaky` failures: Batched PR\\n   173→\\n   174→1. Create branch `fix/e2e-flaky-<run-id-or-date>`\\n   175→2. Apply fixes to ALL flaky test files (one branch, one PR):\\n   176→   - Agent asked for confirmation -> append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prompt\\n   177→   - Agent wrote to wrong path -> be more explicit about paths in prompt\\n   178→   - Agent committed when shouldn't -> add \\\"Do not commit\\\" to prompt\\n   179→   - Checkpoint wait timeout -> increase timeout argument\\n   180→   - Agent timeout (signal: killed) -> increase per-test timeout, simplify prompt\\n   181→3. Run verification:\\n   182→   ```bash\\n   183→   mise run test:e2e:canary   # Must pass\\n   184→   mise run fmt && mise run lint\\n   185→   ```\\n   186→4. If canary fails, investigate and adjust. If unfixable, fall back to issue creation.\\n   187→5. Commit and create PR:\\n   188→   ```bash\\n   189→   gh pr create \\\\\\n   190→     --title \\\"fix(e2e): make flaky tests more resilient\\\" \\\\\\n   191→     --body \\\"<structured body with per-test changes, re-run evidence, run link>\\\"\\n   192→   ```\\n   193→\\n   194→#### For `real-bug` failures: Issue (with dedup)\\n   195→\\n   196→1. **Search existing issues first:**\\n   197→   ```bash\\n   198→   gh issue list --search \\\"is:open label:e2e <TestName>\\\" --json number,title,url\\n   199→   ```\\n   200→\\n   201→2. **If matching issue exists:** Add a comment with new evidence:\\n   202→   ```bash\\n   203→   gh issue comment <number> --body \\\"<re-run results, verification details, run link, new evidence>\\\"\\n   204→   ```\\n   205→   Note \\\"Verified still failing — reproduced in N/N re-runs\\\" plus any new diagnostic details.\\n   206→\\n   207→3. **If no matching issue:** Create new:\\n   208→   ```bash\\n   209→   gh issue create \\\\\\n   210→     --title \\\"E2E: <TestName> fails — <brief symptom>\\\" \\\\\\n   211→     --label \\\"bug,e2e\\\" \\\\\\n   212→     --body \\\"<structured body>\\\"\\n   213→   ```\\n   214→\\n   215→   Issue body includes:\\n   216→   - Test name, agent(s), CI run link (if available), re-run results\\n   217→   - Failure summary (